                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-04-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 211.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 339, of the 4th ultimo, I
                    have to say that the Acting Attorney-General of the United States states that he
                    has forwarded to the United States attorney for the northern district of Ohio
                    the papers relating to the apparently fraudulent naturalization of Giuseppe
                    Divito, with instructions to investigate the case and, if the evidence is
                    obtainable, to institute criminal proceedings against the persons involved.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
